Hungary Ruling Party Sees Decline in Support, Nepszabadsag Says

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-05-12T06:27:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/hungary-ruling-party-sees-decline-in-support-nepszabadsag-says.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s Fidesz party lost support this month,  Nepszabadsag 
 reported , citing an Ipsos poll.  Fidesz was favored by 24 percent of those questioned, down
from 26 percent last month and the lowest percentage since
winning elections in April 2010, the newspaper said.  Support for the Socialist Party, the biggest opposition
group, was 12 percent and 53 percent were undecided or said they
didn’t plan to vote, Nepszabadsag said.  The poll was conducted between May 2 and 9 among 1,500
people, the newspaper added in its online edition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Kirkland in  London  at 
 skirkland@bloomberg.net . 